  "text": "Facilities for malaria microscopy are usually available at the hospital and the private clinics while RDTs are mainly used at the peripheral clinics. The community chemical shops are usually the first point of seeking medical care in the community and malaria diagnosis in the shops is mainly presumptive [CITATION_1] . Currently, Artesunate-amodiaquine is the first line drug for the treatment of uncomplicated malaria in Ghana.",
